The paper deals with the application of non-negative matrix factorization (NMF) to extract physical meaningful sources from temperature time series collected during a thermal manufacturing process. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and artificial intelligence (AI) to analyze the data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of the NMF algorithm, which falls under the category of numerical optimization and nonlinear equations, making cs.NE (Numerical Analysis) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of knowledge-based initialization strategy, which involves the use of expert knowledge to guide the algorithm, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with the analysis of physical phenomena and process variables, which falls under the category of systems and control, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of data collected during the series production of casting parts for the automobile industry, which falls under the category of software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) another likely category.
